                    The first four lines of <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3575Mashaf">Maṣḥafa
                                                  saʿātāt</title>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    This book has been disbound and rebound in disorder. What remains are two stitches, but very incomplete. Many quires have been “repaired” with stab stitches, making impossible an analysis of the original architecture of the codex
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#107v" facs="108">Fol. 107v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    note about a person who received a loan from the church of Abbo
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    marginal notation to mark sections;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <locus target="#41 #67" facs="041 067">Fols. 41, 67</locus>
                    <desc>
                    white thread is sewn into the fore edge to mark content as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
